---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const siteOrigin = Astro.site ? new URL(Astro.site).origin : '';
const canonicalUrl = siteOrigin ? `${siteOrigin}/about/` : undefined;
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="About Scam Avenger: we help you find where to report scams, fraud, and corruption. We do not take reports—we point you to official channels (FTC, IC3, CFPB)."
  keywords="Scam Avenger, report scam, report fraud, where to report scam, consumer protection, FTC IC3 CFPB"
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
>
  <div class="about-hero">
    <img
      src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1450101499163-c8848c66ca85?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80"
      alt=""
      width="1000"
      height="320"
      class="about-hero-img"
    />
    <div class="about-hero-overlay">
      <h1 class="about-hero-title">About Scam Avenger</h1>
      <p class="about-hero-tagline">We help you find where to report scams, fraud, and corruption.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>Scam Avenger helps you find the right place to report scams and corruption. We explain common scam types and link you to official government and trusted reporting channels.</p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Explain how different scams work and what to do if you’re targeted.</li>
    <li>Point you to the correct official form or agency (e.g. FTC, IC3, CFPB, IRS, Oversight.gov) based on your situation.</li>
    <li>Keep a news feed of scam and consumer-protection updates.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don’t do</h2>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> take reports ourselves. We don’t collect your personal information or forward your complaint. We only help you find and use the right official U.S. (and future) channels to report.</p>

  <h2>Coverage</h2>
  <p>We currently focus on the United States. More countries may be added later. All links go to official or trusted sources.</p>

  <h2 id="link-to-us">Link to us</h2>
  <p>If you run a blog, news site, or resource page and want to link to Scam Avenger, you’re welcome to use the following. This helps people find where to report scams and can help our site get discovered.</p>
  <p><strong>Suggested anchor text:</strong> “where to report scams”, “report fraud USA”, “Scam Avenger”, or “report scams (FTC, IC3)”.</p>
  <p><strong>Copy-paste HTML:</strong></p>
  <pre class="link-snippet"><code>&lt;a href="https://scamenger.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Where to report scams and fraud in the USA&lt;/a&gt;</code></pre>
  <p>For a specific scam type, use <code>https://scamenger.com/us/scams/<em>slug</em>/</code> (e.g. <code>/us/scams/phishing/</code>, <code>/us/scams/romance/</code>).</p>

  <p><a href="/">← Back to Home</a></p>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0 calc(-1 * var(--space-lg)) var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
    max-width: calc(100% + 2 * var(--space-lg));
  }

  .about-hero-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 220px;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    background: var(--color-border);
  }

  .about-hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65) 0%, transparent 55%);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-hero-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  }

  .about-hero-tagline {
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .link-snippet {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .link-snippet code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
  }
</style>
